<HEADLINE> Singapore's Ruling Party Wins One More Seat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The ruling People's Action
Party (PAP) has won the single-seat constituency of Kampong Glam
in the general election today.
</P>
<P>
In Kampong Glam ward, PAP candidate Loh Meng See beat the
Democratic Progress Party (DPP) candidate Tan Lead Shake 13,446
votes to 4,598, while 604 votes were rejected.
</P>
<P>
At the close of the poll at 20:00 local time (1200 GMT), 95.86
percent of Singapore's 765,332 voters in all contested Electoral
Divisions had voted.
</P>
<P>
This is the PAP's 48th seat in the 83-member parliament because
the party had already secured 47 seats on the nomination day on
December 23 last year as other parties failed to field candidates
in nine of the 24 constituencies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
