<HEADLINE> PAP Wins One More Parliament Seat in Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's ruling People's
Action Party (PAP) won the single-seat ward of Boon Lay, beating
the National Solidarity Party (NSP) in today's voting.
</P>
<P>
PAP candidate Goh Chee Wee defeated NSP candidate Christopher
Neo 12,407 votes to 6,362. Rejected votes numbered 505.
</P>
<P>
This is PAP's 49th seat in the 83-member parliament. 
</P>
