<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Exports of Flowers, Fruits, Vegetables </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's Horticulture
Promotion Council (HPC) today said that a total of 7,393 tonnes
of cut flowers, fruits and vegetables had been exported since the
beginning of the 1996/97 horticulture season in July.
</P>
<P>
HPC's Chief Executive Stanley Heri said this year Zimbabwe
expects to export 15,000 tonnes of flowers, 3,000 tonnes more
than last year.
</P>
<P>
Producers had indicated that this year they would export to
the Far East, South Africa and the United States in addition to
the European market, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hleri said ''Annually, during the festive holidays we
experience pressure of work due to disruptions at the auctions
when they close for some days."
</P>
<P>
He said that on Christmas day of this year, two additional
planes hired from South Africa Airways helped transport the
horticultural produce. 
</P>
</TEXT>
