<HEADLINE> UNDP Threatens To Withdraw From Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Development
Program (UNDP) has put pressure on Nigeria to ensure the success
of its programs in the country.
</P>
<P>
An UNDP official said the organization said it would withdraw
from financing or co-financing development programs if any of its
programs in the country fails to record at least 80 percent
success.
</P>
<P>
However, the official did not give details about the
threatened withdrawal such as the deadline for the required 80
percent success. He neither disclosed the total number of UNDP
development program underway in Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
According to Malam Ibrahim Huseini, UNDP program manager with
the Kaduna State Environmental Protection Authority, UNDP is
sponsoring or co-sponsoring five development programs in the
state, an industrial center in northern Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The programs involve mass literacy, statistics, women in
development, small-scale industries and environmental
development.
</P>
<P>
He said the involvement of the grassroots in UNDP program
formulation is a deliberate strategy aimed at ensuring the
success of the programs in the country's rural areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
