<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Consumer Complaints Increase in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Athens, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Greek consumers made a record
number of complaints in 1996, the country's biggest consumer
organization Inka reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to Inka, 66,920 complaints were recorded by the
organization in 1996, 11,245 related to the rising cost of living,
and 10,382 about food adulteration.
</P>
<P>
Complaints relating to the Public Power Organization, the
tourism sector and the entertainment industry were also on the
increase in 1996, while complaints about the Hellenic
Telecommunications Organizations were less than those in previous
years, though it still ranked third in the 1996 consumer
complaints' list.
</P>
<P>
Consumer complaints relating to such products as insurance and
bank services as well as local government organizations also
recorded an increase in 1996 compared to previous years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
