<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-02 17:55 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Police: Friedman Has Accomplice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Israeli police said today
that Noam Friedman, the soldier who opened fire on crowded
Palestinians in the center of Hebron Wednesday, had an
accomplice.
</P>
<P>
According to an Israel Television report this evening, Yuval
Jibri, a 21-year-old soldier who serves in the same army
unit with Friedman, "is suspected collusion and failure to
prevent a crime."
</P>
<P>
Police today asked Petach Tikvah Magistrate's Court near Tel
Aviv, where the hearing on the shooting incident took place, to
extend the custody of both soldiers for 45 days.
</P>
<P>
Only Friedman appeared in the court today, when he told
the court that he wanted to show that Prime Minister
Binyamin Netanyahu "does not represent the people."
</P>
<P>
He said that he felt compelled to act to prevent the handover
of Hebron, which has been the subject of intensive talks between
Israel and the Palestinians for the past few weeks.
</P>
<P>
Friedman stated that he regretted over the fact that he only
wounded Arabs and did not kill them, saying he acted alone and
his actions were also to avenge Israelis killed by Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
At least seven Palestinians were wounded by bullets fired by
Friedman through his M-16 rifle, before three other soldiers
overpowered him.
</P>
<P>
According to Israeli army and Police officials, Friedman had
nothing in his personal file restricting his carrying of a
weapon.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Radio reported this morning that a psychologist from
the city of Ma'aleh Adumim where Friedman lived, recommended
that he not be accepted for military service due to his
psychological problems.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, three of the seven the Palestinians wounded during
shooting attack still remain in hospital today, and doctors
said they are expected to be released within a week.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, the Islamic Jihad Movement today
distributed a leaflet vowing revenge for the attack, stressing
"no crime of the enemy against our innocent people will pass
without a punishment."
</P>
<P>
Israeli media reports said that the militant wing of Hamas,
or the Islamic Resistance Movement, also vowed to take revenge for
the shooting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
