but the official said that Ghanaian representatives have already
visited Nigeria to understand the operations of the commission
while Kenya has also signified interest.
</P>
<P>
"Presently, we have about seven African countries that want us
to help them," he said, quoted by a TV report tonight.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria is currently leading the African Sub-Group of
International Road Safety, which comprises Nigeria, Cote
d'Irvoire, Ghana, Gambia, Angola, Mali, Niger, Gabon, Benin
and Sierra Leone. 
