<HEADLINE> One Foreign Tourist Killed, Four Injured in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 2 (Xinhua) -- A Belgian female tourist was
killed and four French tourists injured in a traffic accident in
southern Egypt today.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy happened when a tourist bus with 12 passengers
and a truck collided in front of a tourist center of Swiss
Village in Hurghada, 400 kilometers south of the Egyptian capital
 of Cairo, the Egyptian MENA news agency reported.
