<HEADLINE> Less Passengers Pass Geneva Airport in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The Geneva Airport saw less
passengers in 1996 despite a 2.2 percent increase of aircraft
landings and takeoffs in the same year compared with those in
1995, according to provisional results released today.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, a total of 6,186,714 persons passed the Geneva
international airport, 1.3 percent less than the figure of
6,266,911 in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
According to the release, the decline was caused by a decision
taken by Swissair, Switzerland's leading airlines, to conduct
major long distance flights to the country's largest city of
Zurich.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, Telecom '95, a world exposition held in Geneva in
early October in 1995, attracted an extra number of more than
100,000 people to the city that year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
