<DOCNO> XIE19970103.0060 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arab League Condemns Hebron Shooting Incident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 2 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League today condemned a
shooting committed by an Israeli soldier as "heinous crime"
against unarmed Palestinians in the West Bank town of Hebron and
urged better security for Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
The League's General Secretariat warned that such a criminal
act is likely to increase tension and violence in the region.
</P>
<P>
In a statement on the incident, the Cairo-based league urged
Israel to honor the agreements it signed with the Palestinians and
asked the international community to force Israel to implement
them.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the incident to the February 25 al-Ibrahimi Mosque
massacre in Hebron in 1995, the statement said it followed "with
deep anger and condemnation" the criminal incident which occurred
in Hebron on the morning of the first day of the new year.
</P>
<P>
A year ago, an Israeli soldier opened fire at Palestinians in a
crowded marketplace there, killing and wounding a number of them.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the incident demonstrates how fragile the
security situation is in Hebron and the Palestinian territories.
</P>
<P>
It demanded the creation of an international mechanism to
provide protection for Arabs in occupied Arab territories against
terrorist attacks by Israeli settlers. It also called for
disarming the Israeli settlers in the Palestinian areas.
</P>
<P>
The General Secretariat urged the U.S. and Russia, the two
sponsors of the peace process, and the European Union to shoulder
their responsibilities for bolstering the peace process and making
Israel honor its peace commitments.
</P>
<P>
Noam Friedman, an Israeli soldier, opened fire on crowded
Palestinians in the center of Hebron Wednesday, wounding at least
seven Palestinians, before three other soldiers overpowered him.
</P>
<P>
During the hearing on the shooting incident today, Friedman
told the court that he felt compelled to act to prevent the
handover of Hebron, which has been the subject of intensive talks
between Israel and the Palestinians for the past few weeks.
</P>
<P>
Friedman stated that he regretted over the fact that he only
wounded Arabs and did not kill them, saying he acted alone and
his actions were also to avenge Israelis killed by Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Israel and the Palestinians are trying to clinch a deal to
implement the much-delayed Israeli troop withdrawal from Hebron
where 450 Jewish settlers live among 200,000 Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
The redeployment was put off after a wave of suicide bombings
in Israel in February and March. It was further delayed due to Prime
Minister Binyamin Netanyahu's demand for better protection for
Jewish settlers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
