<HEADLINE> First Futures Exchange Moves into Pudong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Cereals and Oil
Exchange has become the first futures exchange to move from the
old part of Shanghai into the Pudong New Area, an emerging
financial district across the Huangpu River.
</P>
<P>
"Futures market is bound to come into its own in Pudong in the
city government's strategy of moving all of its production factor
markets into the area, " said the city's deputy mayor, Chen
Liangyu.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Cereals and Oil Exchange has had a total turnover
of 845.4 billion yuan in its tradings of rice, soybean and wheat
since it was set up three years ago, and more than 370 million
tons of cereals and edible oil have changed hands during the
period.
</P>
<P>
Experts predicts that an increasing number of grain growers and
traders will be drawn to the futures trading in grain products,
given the necessity for grain to become a commodity with the good
harvests for the past several years.  
</P>
