<HEADLINE> CPPCC's Achievements In 1996 (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The CPPCC National Committee gave full scope to its function as
a proposal maker in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Since the fourth session of the Eighth CPPCC National
Committee, it has received 2,498 proposals, 2,380 of which were
put on file for consideration, a larger number than for the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
In foreign affairs, the CPPCC National Committee held the first
conference of the 21st Century Forum last year, inviting 24
prominent statesmen and scholars from 18 countries.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the CPPCC National Committee, made his
first trip to Poland, the Netherlands, Austria, Switzerland, and
Russia and had a significant effect on relations between China and
the five European countries, improving China's diplomatic
environment, and increasing the CPPCC's influence worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Some CPPCC vice-chairmen also visited foreign countries and
attended international conferences last year, and some foreign
organizations were invited to visit China.
</P>
<P>
These activities publicized China's reforms, opening-up, and
modernization drive, as well as the system of multi-party
cooperation and consultation under the leadership of the Chinese
Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
In referring to the committee's work in 1997, Liang said that
it will go on to perform its functions and help the communist
party and government maintain political stability and unity,
implementing the Ninth Five-Year Plan (1996-2000) and the
Long-Range Targets for the Year 2010, while increasing socialist
ethical and cultural progress. 
</P>
