<HEADLINE> 7 Russian Tourists Killed In Bus Accident in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Seven Russian tourists were killed
and five injured today when their bus collided with a van on the
road from Cairo to a Red Sea resort city.
</P>
<P>
The Middle East News Agency said that the accident took place
when tourist bus carrying 39 tourists slammed into the van and
then overturned near Ras Gharib, a point on the Gulf of Suez in
eastern Egypt and half way from the capital to Hurghada.
</P>
