<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1500 GMT, January 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin arrived by helicopter
today at his Rus residence outside Moscow, where he will meet with
German Chancellor Helmut Kohl on Saturday, the Kremlin said.
</P>
<P>
During his one-day working visit, Kohl is expected to discuss
bilateral relations and a number of important international issues
with Yeltsin, who returned to the Kremlin late December after his
heart bypass surgery in early November.
</P>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- South African President Nelson Mandela today
denied reports that he is going to make a cabinet reshuffle next
month.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers said "unidentified top officials of the ruling
African National Congress (ANC)" leaked the information, adding
that the announcement will be made at the opening of a parliament
meeting on February 7.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- At least four people were killed and 10 others
injured when a bomb exploded near the residence of Chief Minister
Dr. Farooq Abdullah on high security Gupkar road in Srinagar,
India-held Kashmir, today.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that the explosion, set off by
suspected militants in an abandoned auto-rickshaw, destroyed the
auto-rickshaw and partially damaged six other vehicles, a
residential house and a tea stall near the site of the incident.
</P>
<P>
The blast came barely 48 hours after a bicycle bomb went off
outside the army headquarters on the New Year's day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
