<HEADLINE> The CPPCC's Achievements In 1996 (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) had a
number of clear achievements last year in its political
consultation, democratic supervision, and participation in
political and government affairs.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Liang Jinquan, deputy
secretary-general of the CPPCC National Committee, said that the
CPPCC National Committee's work last year features studies of some
special topics and proposals for state policies.
</P>
<P>
Various CPPCC subcommittees made 40 different reports and
suggestions, focusing on socialist cultural and ethical progress,
united front work, and other significant issues, Liang said.
</P>
<P>
The reports dealt with concerns of the central government, and
many of the suggestions on how to promote ethical and cultural
progress were accepted by the central government, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC National Committee also organized 25 teams of some
500 CPPCC members to go to 21 provinces, municipalities, and
autonomous regions for inspection purposes.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC members put forward some 1,337 suggestions to the
government in 1996, he said.
</P>
