<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-03 15:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Launches First Air Strike on Hezbollah Bases in 1997 (I) (by Shao Jie) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Israeli warplanes carried out
this morning their first air strike on the guerrilla
bases of the pro-Iranian Hezbollah, or Party of God, in
south Lebanon, the first such assault in 1997.
</P>
<P>
No words on casualties were given by security sources, however.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli warplanes fired at least 10 air-to-surface
missiles at targets in Iglim Al-Toffah, a mountain area often
used by Moslem guerrillas of the Shiite Hezbollah as a
springboard to launch attacks against Israeli forces.
</P>
<P>
In the first bombing at 9:20 a.m. (07:20 GMT) and
the second five minutes later, Israeli warplanes fired eight
missiles at the hills of Sojoud, Rihan and Loweizeh.
</P>
<P>
The air raids followed intensive fire by Israeli artillery
at Jabel Al-Rafih and vicinities of the villages of Sojoud
and Rihan, which started at 7:00 a.m. (05:00 GMT) and lasted for
two hours and a half.
</P>
<P>
Israeli troops in the positions located in the middle sector of
the so-called "security zone" resumed the bombardments at 10:00
a.m. (08:00 GMT) targeting Iglim Al-Toffah, some 60 kilometers
southeast of Beirut, according to the security sources.
</P>
<P>
The shellings, with 120-mm and 150-mm mortars, were
concentrated on Jabel Al-Rafih, Tallat Mlita and Jabel Al-Safik.
</P>
<P>
At 11:05 a.m. (09:05 GMT), Israeli helicopters started
hovering over Jabel Al-Rafih and Tallat Mlita. And 25 minutes
later, the helicopters fired two missiles at the height of
Sojoud.
</P>
<P>
In the ensuing 30 minutes, Israeli warplanes also launched
three successive air raids in Iglim Al-Toffah and fired
machineguns at suspected targets, security sources in the
area reported.
</P>
<P>
From earlier this morning and until noon, Israeli
warplanes carried out frequent reconnaissance flights over a
wide range between the south Lebanese coast town of Naqoura
to Iglim Al-Toffah to the east.
</P>
<P>
The security sources estimated that about 18 Israeli
helicopters carried out the air strike and reconnaissance missions
 over south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Resistance, the military wing of Hezbollah,
announced that in retaliation for the Israeli aggressions, its
fighters launched counterattacks this morning on the Israeli
positions at Sojoud and Bir Kalab.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970103.0086 </DOCNO>
