<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-03 15:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Launches First Air Strike on Hezbollah </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a statement broadcast through Hezbollah's radio, the
guerrilla group said that its fighters used machineguns and
rocket-propelled grenades in the counterattack, inflicting
casualties upon the enemy troops.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Radio confirmed that an Israeli officer and a
soldier were injured in the morning attacks in the south
Lebanese buffer zone, and announced that Israeli warplanes
launched air raids at Iglim Al-Toffah.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the Iranian-backed Hezbollah and the
Israeli client South Lebanon Army (SLA) militia swapped this
morning the remains of two militiamen for two dead guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah received the bodies of the two guerrillas on the
border at 11:30 a.m. (09:30 GMT) and transferred them to Beirut in
a convoy comprising three ambulances and five private vehicles.
</P>
<P>
The Shiite fundamentalist party, which spearheads a guerrilla
warfare against the Israeli forces in south Lebanon, handed over
the bodies of the two SLA soldiers to officials of the
International Committee of the Red Cross in a Beirut suburb at
the same time.
</P>
<P>
The 2,500-strong militia backed by some 1,000 Israeli troops
is patrolling the 1,100-square-kilometer "security zone" the
Jewish state established in 1985.
</P>
<P>
Hit-and-run attacks by Moslem guerrillas and bombardments by
Israeli forces constitute a daily scene on the last active
battlefront of the Arab-Israeli conflict.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah says that its guerrillas killed 45 Israelis and
wounded 211 others in clashes in south Lebanon in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah fighters carried out 765 military operations
throughout the year, which also resulted in killing 34 SLA
militiamen and the wounding 72 others. The Islamic Resistance
suffered a loss of 47 lives, according to a Hezbollah statement.
</P>
<P>
Israel said that 28 Israeli soldiers were killed and
102 others were wounded in guerrilla operations against its
forces, and two soldiers died and two others injured in
different incidents in the occupied enclave in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
It also confirmed that 20 SLA militiamen were killed and
58 others wounded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
