<HEADLINE> Tianjin's Major Ethylene Project Passes State Appraisal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 3 (Xinhua) -- An ethylene facility of Tianjin
United Chemical Company, which has a designed production capacity of
140,000 tons, has been accepted after appraisal done jointly by
experts from China National Petrochemical Corporation and Tianjin
Municipality.
</P>
<P>
Listed as one of the state key construction projects for the
1991-95 period, the project started building in 1992 and was
completed in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The facility was put into trial operation in December of 1995
and produced 81,000 tons of quality ethylene and 46,000 tons of
quality polyethylene, generating 560 million yuan in output value
during one-year trial operation.
</P>
<P>
Experts on the appraisal panel say that the facility is
equipped with advanced equipment and technology, and all its
indexes have met designing requirements, and has shown safe and
steady performances in trial operation, and has met state-set
standards. 
