<HEADLINE> ITF Names Sampras, Graf as World Champions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Pete Sampras and Steffi Graf were
selected as the world champions by the International Tennis
Federation here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Sampras has won this title for four straight years while Steffi
Graf has taken the women's award for a record seventh time.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, who ties Ivan Lendl's record of four world champion
awards, won one of the Grand Slam titles, the U.S. Open, this year
while Graf triumphed at every one she contested, the French and
U.S. Opens and Wimbledon.
</P>
<P>
Graf overtakes Martina Navratilova who was named world champion
six times, in 1979 and between 1982 and 1986. The German star
first had the award in 1987 and has since collected it
in '88, '89, '90, '93 and '95.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the awards Friday, the ITF also created its first
world champions for doubles.
</P>
<P>
Todd Woodbridge and Mark Woodforde of Australia, who added the
Olympic title to their fourth Wimbledon and second U.S. Open
triumphs, are the ITF men's doubles world champions and Americans
Lindsay Davenport and Mary Joe Fernandez, who teamed up for a
French Open triumph as well as winning the WTA Tour Championship,
receive the women's title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
