<HEADLINE> Hong Kong, Singapore Exchange Engineering Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 3 (Xinhua) -- At the beginning of 1997, Hong
Kong greeted another group of engineering students from Singapore
under an annual exchange program between two universities.
</P>
<P>
Eight students of the National University of Singapore arrived
in Hong Kong Thursday to take up training jobs in local industries
in the next six months. In return, eight students of the
University of Hong Kong will go to Singapore this summer for
two-month working placement.
</P>
<P>
Majoring in engineering, they form the 24th batch of
participants in the student exchange scheme, jointly launched by
the two universities since 1974.
</P>
<P>
Ng Chin Lee, a Singaporean student taking part in this year's
exchange program, believed that the industrial training experience
would broaden his horizon, help him make friends, and above all,
offer him an opportunity to eyewitness the historic moment on July
1, 1997, when China resumes its exercises of sovereignty over Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Ng and other seven third-year students were chosen from 70
applicants in the Faculty of Engineering of the Singaporean
university.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two decades, more than 400 students have
benefited from the exchange scheme, said W. P. J. Brandon, dean of
students of the University of Hong Kong. "Either Hong Kong or
Singaporean students can gain an insight into industrial and
technological development in the other economy," said Brandon.
</P>
<P>
Each year the group of Hong Kong students carry out researches
on a theme topic during the trip to Singapore, such as environment
issues in Singapore, Singapore industries, high technology in
Singapore and comparative study between Singapore and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The dean said that the helpful program is the oldest student
exchange scheme developed by the University of Hong Kong, which
has launched a dozen with universities in Australia, Britain,
Canada and the United States.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
