States defeated Jonas Bjorkman of Sweden 6-1, 6-7 (2-7), 7-6
(17-15), while Australian Scott Draper beat Karol Kucera of
Slovakia 6-4, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge is the only seed left in contention.
</P>
<P>
The 32-draw ATP Tour event, which is being played on the same
Rebound Ace courts used for the Australian Open, continues through
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Open starts Jan. 13 at the National Tennis
Center in Melbourne. 
