<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Separating Banks from Trust, Investment Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 3 (Xinhua) -- China's four largest state-owned
banks basically withdrew from the trust and investment business by
the end of last year, the People's Bank of China said here today.
</P>
<P>
Since November, 148 trust and investment companies now operate
apart from the banks - 46 from the Industrial and Commercial Bank,
36 from the Agricultural Bank, 33 from the Bank of China, and
another 33 from the China Construction Bank. Another 33 have been
approved for transfer, the central bank said.
</P>
<P>
The four banks previously had a total of 186 trust and
investment firms, but are now barred from the business under the
country's 1995 Commercial Bank Law.
</P>
<P>
Asset evaluations are still being done so that the trust and
investment companies can be transferred, the central bank said,
and the work has gone very smoothly, according to the central bank.
</P>
<P>
Up to some 100 billion yuan in assets of the trust and
investment companies have been transferred in full, with no losses
or payment problems during the process, the central bank noted.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
