<HEADLINE> Philippines to Set Up New Overseas Embassies, Consulate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government plans
to set up three additional embassies and a consulate in foreign
countries this year.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine News Agency quoted Foreign Affairs Secretary
Domingo Siazon today as saying that the country intends to
establish embassies soon in Laos, Jordan and Czech, and a
consulate in Guangzhou, China.
</P>
<P>
Siazon said the Guangzhou consulate will complement the
existing Philippine embassy in Beijing and the consulate general
in Xiamen City.
</P>
<P>
He said the decision to set up an embassy in Laos is in
preparation for Laos' admission to the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
The proposed embassy in Prague aims to consolidate the
Philippine diplomatic outreach in Eastern Europe while the planned
embassy in Jordan is to better protect and serve the welfare of
the Filipinos in that country, he said.
</P>
<P>
Presently, the Philippine ambassador to Israel is also
accredited as non-resident envoy to Jordan.  
</P>
