<HEADLINE> Chinese Puts 10 Billion Yuan Into Housing for Teachers In 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 3 (Xinhua) -- China has put ten billion yuan
(about 1.2 billion US dollars) into housing for teachers, an
official with the State Education Commission said today.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 million square meters of the housing were added in
1996, the official said, bringing the average space for each
member of a teacher's family to eight square meters.
</P>
<P>
For years Chinese teachers have been troubled by limited living
space, so improved housing conditions and other perks could be an
effective way to prevent them from changing professions, he said.
</P>
<P>
How to stablize the number of faculty members was a major topic
at a meeting on education management last year.
</P>
<P>
The past year has seen some progress in teacher training, and
over 70 percent of the one million headmasters in primary and
secondary schools in China have got qualifications certificates.
</P>
</TEXT>
