<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Achieves Full Telephone Number Portability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong has achieved full
portability of telephone numbers using the intelligent network and
database technique, Hong Kong Telecommunications Authority said
today.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is the first city in the world to achieve full number
portability.
</P>
<P>
"To the consumers, this means that all fixed telephone users
can keep their numbers wherever they move their homes or offices
within Hong Kong," a spokesman for the Office of the
Telecommunications Authority (OFTA) said.
</P>
<P>
"They can also keep their numbers if they change their
subscription from one telephone company to another," he added.
</P>
<P>
OFTA will conduct a study in the near future to consider the
applicability and desirability of introducing number portability
to mobile telephone services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
