<HEADLINE> HK People More Confident of Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong people are becoming
more confident of the future as the date for Hong Kong's handover
approaching, according to result of an opinion poll conducted this
week.
</P>
<P>
The telephone survey of 520 people found that 77.9 percent of
respondents were confident about Hong Kong's future, compared with
that of 66 percent in the previous survey conducted three weeks
ago.
</P>
<P>
The number of respondents saying they were not confident fell
to 9.6 percent from 10.2 percent, the survey revealed.
</P>
<P>
The survey is conducted every month by the University of Hong
Kong. 
