<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan Condemns Terrorist Explosion in Syria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Crown Prince Hassan,
the Regent, made a telephone call to Syrian President Hafez
al-Assad Thursday night and condemned the terrorist explosion in
Damascus, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Nine people were killed and 44 others wounded when a bomb
exploded aboard a bus in the Syrian capital of Damascus Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Regent said that Jordan will always take the same
stand with Syria in fighting terrorist activities.
</P>
<P>
Hassan also reiterated that Jordan will fight terrorists
any time and at any place and expressed condolences to the
victims.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the terrorists behind the action were
aimed at harming Syria's stance in its request for a lasting
and just peace.
</P>
<P>
Assad reportedly said that the cycle of violence in the region
should be utterly eliminated. 
</P>
