<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Strengthens Cooperation With Interpol </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 3 (Xinhua) - Vietnam has strengthened
cooperation with the International Police Organization (Interpol)
in the past five years, the Vietnamese Interior Ministry has said.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's Interpol office has received around 500 investigation
requests from both domestic and foreign channels and about 800
warrants to track down and arrest criminals or suspects per year
on average, the ministry said in a report at a conference
reviewing cooperation between Vietnam and Interpol held Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report said the Interpol's Vietnam office has sent more
than 400 replies from domestic investigation. The office has also
stepped up efforts in preventing and combating crimes, especially
economic crimes related to international economic cooperation and
investment.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has also cooperated with Interpol in fighting money
laundering, use of counterfeit money, fake treasury bills and
personal documents for criminal purposes, drug trafficking and
abuse, as well as other crimes committed by overseas Vietnamese or
foreigners who came to Vietnam, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
