<HEADLINE> Syrian-Lebanese Coordination Committee to Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The Syrian-Lebanese
coordination committee will meet in Damascus on January 11 under
the co-chairmanship of Syrian Prime Minister Mahmoud Zouebi and
his Lebanese counterpart Rafiq Hariri, according to Syrian
official sources here today.
</P>
<P>
The meetings are aimed at evaluating the process of economic and
commercial integration and the implementation of agreements
reached over the past year and ways of enhancing cooperation and
coordination in the economic and trade fields in accordance with
the treaty of brotherhood and cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The treaty calls for strengthening bilateral relations in all
fields with the ultimate objective of achieving the stage of
political and economic integration.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, diplomatic sources here said that Syria and
Lebanon will review the latest developments, especially the
peace process, and ways of coordinating political stances in the
face of future developments.
</P>
<P>
They will also discuss the current attempts to separate the
Syrian and Lebanese tracks, and the drawing up of a common
strategy at the Arab, regional and international levels.
</P>
<P>
Hariri was quoted as saying Thursday that the Damascus
meeting will discuss matters of mutual concern, including
industry, petroleum, agriculture and transport.
</P>
<P>
He said that two agreements on the encouragement of
investments and abolition of dual taxation are due to be signed
during the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
