<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The Kaduna home of Nigeria former
Head of State, Major-General Muhammadu Buhari was patronized by
unknown bandits on Tuesday, the New Year Eve, the "Guardian"
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Six security guards serving in Buhari's house in the Angwar
Rimi Government Reservation Area in Kaduna City in northern
Nigeria have been arrested by investigating security agents, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Buhari, also the chairman of the all-powerful Petroleum Trust
Fund was not at home when the bandits struck, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The bandits ransacked his bedroom after breaking through the
window and took away electronic items worth of thousands of naira
in the living room. They also reportedly destroyed some personal
belongings of Buhari.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said the bandits may have resolved to vent
their spleen on the property upon the absence of Buhari.
</P>
<P>
Buhari reportedly returned after the bandits have left. He
then woke up the security guards who were asleep on the floor
beside the main gate. It is suspected that they were all drugged.
</P>
