<HEADLINE> Stock Exchange of Thailand Index Falls 1.95 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The broad-based Stock Exchange
of Thailand (SET) index today lost a further 15.66 points, or 1.95
percent, to close at 787.47 points, dropping well below the
800-point psychological barrier.
</P>
<P>
Today's Thai bourse index drop followed a plunge of 28.44
points, or 3.42 percent on Thursday, the first trading day of this
year. The SET index closed at 803.13 points on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Today's trading was worth 3.065 billion baht (120.2 million US
dollars), compared with 2.25 billion baht (88.24 million US
dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
On September 11, 1992, the SET index registered 801.90 points,
the lowest in the last four years.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the SET index lost a total of 520.30 points, or
39.31 percent.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that share prices are suffering from the impact
of last year's poor bourse performance and that the new
government's economic measures will not be able to produce visible
positive results in the near future.
</P>
<P>
Investors are concerned about the country's high current
account deficit, export zero-growth and other poor economic
indicators.  
</P>
</TEXT>
