<HEADLINE> Four Killed in Bomb Blast in India-held Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- At least four people were
killed and 10 others injured when a bomb exploded near the
residence of Chief Minister Dr. Farooq Abdullah on high- security
Gupkar road in Srinagar, India-held Kashmir, today.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that the explosion, set off by
suspected militants in an abandoned auto-rickshaw, destroyed the
auto-rickshaw and partially damaged six other vehicles, a
residential house and a tea stall near the site of the incident.
</P>
<P>
The blast came barely 48 hours after a bicycle bomb went off
outside the army headquarters on the New Year's day.
</P>
<P>
Minister of State for Home Ali Mohammad Sagar and other civil
and police officers rushed to the spot and supervised the shifting
of the injured to the hospital.
</P>
<P>
So far no militant outfit has claimed responsibility for the
blast.  
</P>
</TEXT>
