<HEADLINE> Turkey to Host D-8 FM Meeting in Istanbul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers from eight
developing Moslem countries, known as "D-8", are to meet
Saturday in Istanbul, the largest city in Turkey, to discuss ways
to strengthen cooperation in all fields.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Islamist Prime Minister Necmettin Erbakan is expected
to chair the opening ceremony of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will also review the preparations for a D-8
summit meeting scheduled to be held in Turkey in the first
quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister meeting in Istanbul will be the second
gathering of the "D-8" countries. The first was held in Ankara by
high-ranking officials from the member countries, who agreed to
set up the D-8 headquarters in Istanbul to handle its daily work.
</P>
<P>
The D-8 bloc, which groups Bangladesh, Egypt, Indonesia,
Iran, Malaysia, Nigeria, Pakistan and Turkey, was launched by
Turkey after the pro-Islamic Welfare Party led by Necmettin
Erbakan came to power in 1996.
</P>
<P>
At the Conference on Cooperation and Development held in
Istanbul in October last year, Erbakan proposed the creation of
the D-8 group, which was officially formed in November.
</P>
<P>
The Turkey-launched group has come across severe
criticism from other Moslem countries, especially the Central
Asian nations which are not invited to the bloc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
