<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anhui Expressway Company Purchases New Highway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The Anhui Expressway Company Ltd.,
China's first highway enterprise listed on the overseas stock
market, has purchased the Tianchang section of No. 205 national
highway at a total cost of 210 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The No. 205 highway runs from Shanhaiguan in north China's
Hebei Province, to Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong
Province, passing by Tianchang in east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
Now that it holds the management right of the Tianchang
section, the Anhui Expressway company is bound to gain great
returns, said Wang Shui, chairman of the company, who predicts
that the daily flow of vehicles on the Tianchang section will
reach 8,000 to 9,000 by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The Tianchang section, with a total length of nearly 30 km,
opened on New Year's Day.
</P>
<P>
The road, a first-grade highway only for automobile use, is
also a part of the Nanjing-Lianyungang highway in neighboring
Jiangsu Province. It is expected to stimulate the economic
expansion in northern Jiangsu and the eastern part of Anhui.
</P>
<P>
The Anhui Expressway Company was listed on the Hong Kong Stock
Exchange on November 13, 1996, raising 870 million Hong Kong
dollars of overseas funds.
</P>
<P>
The company now manages a superhighway from Hefei, capital city
of Anhui, to Nanjing, the provincial capital of Jiangsu Province.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
