<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 3 (Xinhua) -- A Sri Lankan passenger
plane en rout from Colombo to Durban and Johannesburg was
grounded for more than four hours at Durban International Airport
on Thursday night because of a bomb scare, informed sources said.
</P>
<P>
South African Broadcast Corporation (SABC) Radio quoted the
sources as saying today that while airborne, the captain received
information that there was a bomb aboard.
</P>
<P>
