<HEADLINE> Jiangsu to Host China's First Postal Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, January 3 (Xinhua) -- China's first festival to honor
the postal system will be held in the city of Gaoyou, the
birthplace of China's postal undertakings, on October 18, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The event will be jointly sponsored by the Ministry of Posts
and Telecommunications, the Jiangsu Provincial Government and the
State Administration of Cultural Relics.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,200 years ago, a courier post was formed in the area
that later became Gaoyou in east China's Jiangsu Province. The
city is also the home of the Yucheng Post, the largest and most
complete ancient postal site in China, and the only postal museum
in the country.
</P>
<P>
The festival will feature trade and auctions of postal products
and seminars. 
</P>
