<HEADLINE> CAPDI Gets ISO9000 Quality System Certificate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The China Aeronautical Project
and Design Institute (CAPDI) was recently awarded the ISO9000
Quality System Certificate by the China Center for Prospecting
Designing Quality Appraisal, thus becoming one of the few
institutes to pass the appraisal process.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1951, the CAPDI is the first multi-discipline
organization engaged in projects and designs for China's aviation
industry.
</P>
<P>
As a class-A state design institute, the CAPDI boasts skilled
professionals, including four master designers, 60 researchers and
350 senior engineers.
</P>
<P>
Over the past decade, the institute has gained design
qualification certificates for 14 services concerning
architecture, aviation, light industry, and others.
</P>
<P>
So far, the CAPDI has won 50 state prizes, 150
ministerial-level awards and received 24 national patents.
</P>
<P>
The institute has also established technical cooperative
relations with more than 30 countries and regions, while building
up business connections with world organizations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
