<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cable TV Booms in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese people have more
choices in watching television programs now that millions of
televisions in both urban and rural areas have cable access.
</P>
<P>
The cable television industry has grown rapidly since it was
initiated in China at the beginning of the 1990s. The country now
has more than 1,200 cable television stations covering 40 million
subscribers in 29 provinces, municipalities and autonomous
regions. The country's total cable TV audience is estimated to be
200 million people.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey shows that the cable TV subscribers spend 40
percent of their television-viewing time tuned in to cable TV
channels. The monthly charge for the service is ten yuan on
average.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Cable TV Station, founded three years ago, is now
the largest cable TV carrier in the country, with 1.82 million
users.
</P>
<P>
An official with the national organization for cable TV
stations said that the cable TV system will become part of the
country's information superhighway once the technologies of
broadband and multimedia are added to it.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the next century, the number of China's cable
TV subscribers will exceed 60 million, and the audience will be
about 300 million people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
