<HEADLINE> Mobile Homes Brought to Jewish Settlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Seven mobile homes were
brought Thursday night to the Artis Hill, adjacent to the Jewish
settlement of Bet El in the West Bank, Israel Radio reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Jewish settlers reportedly set up the "new neighborhood" in
memory of Bet El residents Eta and Ephraim Tzur, killed in
a drive-by shooting attack several weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
People in the mobile homes said they plan to spend the
Sabbath (Saturday) in their new homes in the new community
being called "Maoz Tzur."
</P>
<P>
Following the death of Eta and Ephraim Tzur, the Bet El
community made a request to Israeli Prime Minister Binyamin
Netanyahu to permit the construction of an additional 1,000
housing units on the Artis hilltop.
</P>
<P>
However, fearing rejection from the Palestinians and the
international community, the Israeli government turned down the
request. 
</P>
