<HEADLINE> Mozambique Cuts Charges on International Phone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique cut its international
telephone charges by 10 percent since the first day of 1997, the
third drop during the last 12 months, the Noticia's newspaper
said today.
</P>
<P>
The tariffs on domestic phone calls remain the same, the paper
said.
</P>
<P>
Charges on phone calls from Mozambique to its neighbors fell
from 11,500 medicais to 10,350 meticais per minute.
</P>
<P>
About 12,000 medicais equal to one U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
People calling IDD telephones to Europe or America now should
pay 37,260 or 41,400 medicais per minute separatively.
</P>
<P>
The original payment for calls to Europe and America were
41,400 and 46,000 per minute relatively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
