<DOCNO> XIE19970103.0186 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number of Elderly Increasing in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The number of elderly people in
Tianjin is increasing by 5.27 percent yearly, 2.8 times more than
the total population growth rate in the city, according to a
recent survey.
</P>
<P>
At present, more than 12 percent of citizens in Tianjin are
over 60, with the total number standing at 1.16 million, 260,000
more than five years ago, according to the survey.
</P>
<P>
One third of the 2.8 million households in this major
industrial city each have at least one elderly person.
</P>
<P>
The statistics also show that the number of people aged over 80
have increased during the past five years, and 60 of them are over
the age of 100.
</P>
<P>
"This aging process has caused great concern among the related
government departments, and now we are making efforts to allow the
aged to live better lives," said a local official.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, a local code protecting the rights
of the elderly has been issued in Tianjin, which is the first of
its kind in China.
</P>
<P>
Some 249 nursing homes as well as many hospitals, entertainment
centers and schools for the aged have been established throughout
the city, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Taking good care of the aged is a good tradition of our
nation, and to create a better living condition for the aged is
not only our responsibility, but also part of our drive to promote
cultural and ethical progress," the official said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
