<HEADLINE> Washington Pulls out of Auckland Tennis Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Wimbledon finalist MaliVai
Washington of the United States was forced to quit next week's New
Zealand Open tennis tournament by a recurring back problem.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old has played in the ATP tour's Auckland
tournament five times, reaching the final in 1992 and 1993.
Ranked 20th in the world, Washington would have been the fourth
seed for the event which begins Monday.
</P>
<P>
Tournament director Graham Pearce said Friday that Washington
called from the United States to say he could not get on the plane.
</P>
<P>
The injury had forced him to withdraw during one tournament
last year and scratch from another. It also troubled him during
the season-ending Grand Slam Cup.
</P>
<P>
Washington said how well his back responded to treatment would
determine whether he would be able to compete in the Australian
Open beginning January 13. 
</P>
</TEXT>
