<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines Registers big Increase in Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' merchandise
exports expanded by 29.8 percent in November 1996 compared with a
year ago, the highest year-on-year growth for exports in the year,
the National Statistics Office said today.
</P>
<P>
In a report released here, the statistics office said that the
country's revenue from merchandise exports for November 1996
increased by 423.48 million U.S. dollars to 1.846 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Compared to the previous month, however, a 2 percent seasonal
drop from the October value placed at 1.884 billion dollars was
noted, it said.
</P>
<P>
The office said that cumulative receipts for the first eleven
months amounted to 18.656 billion dollars, up by 17.9 percent from
15.826 billion dollars in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Receipts from electronics and components, accounting for 42.6
percent of the total, increased by 57 percent to 786.56 million
dollars from 500.94 million dollars in the previous year, the
office said.
</P>
<P>
This increase enabled the commodity group to maintain its hold
of the top spot, despite a 0.8 percent dip from the October value
posted at 780.59 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The office said that articles of apparel and clothing
accessories meanwhile remained as the second biggest dollar earner
as purchases reached 188.89 million dollars, up by 8.1 percent
from 174.69 million dollars in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Exports of apparel and clothing accessories accounted for 10.2
percent of the total revenue in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistics office, while the United States
remained the Philippines' biggest market, Japan and Singapore are
the country's second and third biggest ones.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
