<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Tobacco Production Expected to Rise 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's tobacco production is
expected to increase by about 18 percent this year following an
increase in the area under tobacco from 81,300 to 95,400
hectares.
</P>
<P>
In its latest quarterly guide to the economy, the First
Merchant Bank said a higher proportion of the crop was being
grown under irrigation and the average yield was therefore
expected to increase to about 240 million kg from 201.6 milloion
kg in the 1996 auction season.
</P>
<P>
''At an average of 2.94 US Dollars a kg, the revenue in 1996
reached a record 592 million US Dollars, and growers have hopes
that the good demand levels will keep prices firm again in the
auctions that will start in April 1997," said the bank.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe is the world's second largest tobacco exporter,
accounting for 22 percent of world exports. The world's largest
exporter of tobacco is Brazil which commands a quarter of the
world's export market. enditem

