<HEADLINE> Cross-sea Bridges Completed in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Two cross-sea bridges at the
Tianjin Port, the largest in north China, has completed
and passed state assessment.
</P>
<P>
Both of bridges, one a railway passage and the other a highway,
are located at the southern end of the port.
</P>
<P>
The railway bridge is 2,873.45 meters long, with a designed
annual traffic capacity of 35 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The highway bridge, which runs parallel to the railway bridge,
is 1,205 meters long, and designed to accommodate 800 motor
vehicles per hour.
</P>
<P>
Total cost of the bridges is 291.5 million yuan (35.12 million
US dollars), the largest sum for an infrastructure project ever
built at the port.
</P>
<P>
The southern part of the port area is a newly-developed
district which handles petroleum, chemicals, coal and mineral
ore. 
</P>
