<HEADLINE> Work on Modern History of Uygur Ethnic Group Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The first book detailing the
modern history of the Uygur ethnic group has rolled off
press in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The 800,000-character "History of Uygur Ethnic Group" (second
volume) was written by Liu Zhixiao in both Chinese and Uyger
languages. Liu is associated with the Xinjiang Academy of Social
Sciences, where he specializes in the histories of ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
The work describes the development of the Uygur ethnic group
between the 1930s and 1949, when the People's Republic of China
was founded.
</P>
<P>
Critics have called it a systematic analysis and portrayal of
the nationality's historical growth, and political, economic and
cultural situations.
</P>
<P>
The "History of Uygur Ethnic Nationality" (first volume) was
published in 1984. It is a 500,000-character work on the ancient
history of the ethnic group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
