<HEADLINE> India Plans to Strengthen Public Sector Undertakings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- In a bid to catapult some of
the public sector undertakings (PSUS) as multinational companies,
the Indian government plans to empower them to acquire three main
attributes -- state-of-the-art technology, finance and
professional management, an official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Along with this, the government would also help these companies
merge group companies or acquire other public sector units working
in related areas in order to strengthen their core competency and
acquire the global size.
</P>
<P>
For the much-needed financial support for the globalization
efforts of the PSUS majors, the government is planning multiple
options including priority lending by domestic financial
institutions and allowing these companies to tap international
markets through global depository receipts issues.
</P>
<P>
A complete recast of the management of these PSUS by inducting
professionals and granting autonomy to the boards of these
companies is also on the cards.
</P>
<P>
On the technology front, the government's efforts would be to
facilitate quick technology tie-ups by these companies with the
multinational companies. This could be achieved by granting
autonomy to the company boards. Since latest technologies come
with a high price, the strategy would be mainly to join hands with
multinational companies for setting up overseas projects. The PSUS
majors could also make use of their core strengths to bring down
the prices to a realistic level.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
