<HEADLINE> Thai Computer Industry to Keep Booming in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's computer industry is
expected to continue to boom in 1997 in both domestic and export
markets as demand surpasses supply, says the Thai Farmers Research
Center.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's computer exports are expected to enjoy a more than
20-25 percent growth in the new year, while the industry will see
a 15 percent growth in the domestic market, the center says.
</P>
<P>
The center also indicates that the air-conditioner market in
the country will continue to expand this year as more and more
middle class people can afford the products, predicting a 15
percent growth in the domestic market and a 20-25 percent growth
in the export market for the products.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the research center believes that other
commodities, like information technology products, television
sets, cosmetics, vending machines, comic books, milk, fast food,
seasonings, frozen foods, fruit juice, and snacks, will sell well
this year.  
</P>
