<HEADLINE> Steps Mooted to Boost India's Services Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- In a four pronged strategy
submitted to the Finance Ministry, the PHD Chamber of Commerce and
Industry (PHDCCI) has suggested export of services at par with the
merchandise export for giving boost to exports and encouraging
foreign exchange earnings, PHDCCI sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
PHDCCI analysis estimated that services export would constitute
more than 40 percent of their total exports by the turn of the
century and would be a high value commodity in future, PHDCCI
President Binjay Kumar said.
</P>
<P>
To encourage export of services, "service" should be defined to
include any type of professional services including management,
fashion designing, legal, accountancy, consultancy, etc., he said.
</P>
<P>
The PHDCCI president has also urged the need for total tax
exemption for service export instead of 50 percent. 
</P>
