<HEADLINE> 7,779 Argentines Killed in Traffic Accidents in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, January 2 (Xinhua) -- A total of 7,779 Argentines
were killed in traffic accidents in 1996, with an average of 21
deaths a day, said an advocacy group here today.
</P>
<P>
Alberto Silveiro, president of the group "Let us fight for
life," said the death toll of 1996 decreased by 4 percent compared
with the previous year's total of 8,090.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the drop to the mass media's effective campaign
calling for travelers' use of safety belt.
</P>
<P>
Accidents taking place in the province of Buenos Aires claimed
more victims than in other provinces, with 3,428 people killed in
traffic accidents in 1996, he added. 
</P>
