<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Forces Destroy More Tamil Rebel Bases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
have destroyed four more bases of the Tamil rebels of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) in the jungles of the
Eastern Batticaloa district by Thursday evening, according to
military sources today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the troops, assisted by the airforce,
Thursday destroyed three bases -- a women's camp, a rebel workshop
and an administration base.
</P>
<P>
The sources noted that signs indicated that all the camps had
been abandoned in a hurry as the troops advanced on them.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that on the previous day, government troops
attacked another camp which is a medical base. 14 rebels were
killed and 15 others who were injured fled away.
</P>
<P>
The operation, launched in the early hours of December 31 last
year, involved the movement of hundreds of troops into the Eastern
jungles.
</P>
<P>
So far during the offensive, there had been only two casualties
amongst the government troops, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a 13-year guerrilla war for a
separate state in the north and east of the island country.
</P>
</TEXT>
