<HEADLINE> Thailand to Revise Rules for State Enterprise Bond </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Finance Ministry is
expected to revise regulations in order to allow state enterprises
to issue bonds during a year when the government budget has a
surplus, local newspapers reported today.
</P>
<P>
The move aims to stimulate the local debt instrument market by
providing low-risk bonds, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Under the existing law, Thai state enterprises are not allowed
to issue bonds during a year when the government spending is in
surplus.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that the existing law blocks state enterprises,
the main power in the debt instrument market, out of the market.
