<HEADLINE> Private Sector's Role Increasingly Important </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Official paper The New Light of Myanmar today quoted Myanmar
Minister for Finance and Revenue Brigadier-General Win Tin as
saying that savings at private banks had reached 27.76 per cent of
the total savings in the entire country in 1996 up from 12.77 per
cent in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Loans disbursed by private banks rose to 31.85 per cent of the
total loans disbursed by all state-owned and private banks in 1996
up from 15.7 per cent in 1995, the Minister said at the opening
of a private branch bank in Tachilek, Shan State of Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the six state-owned banks, there are 20 local
private banks in Myanmar, of which 7 are permitted to handle
foreign exchange transactions, 5 to deal with credit cards and 4
to apply hire-purchase system.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, foreign banks including two Thai and one Malaysian
banks have agreed with some local private ones in the past few
months to form joint-venture banks in Myanmar, signaling the
country's entry into the second phase of its financial reform,
according to early official report.  
</P>
