<HEADLINE> Shanghai Futures Building under Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The construction of the
Shanghai Futures building is proceeding smoothly, and the Shanghai
Metal Exchange is scheduled to move into the facility in early
1998.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Metal Exchange has invested 800 million yuan
(about 96.4 million US dollars) in the 37-story structure, which
is 187 meters high and has a total floor space of 71,000 square
meters.
</P>
<P>
The 2,000-square meter main trading hall on the fourth floor
features over 600 trading seats.
</P>
<P>
The exchange is an experimental futures exchange, approved by
the State Council, dealing with the non-ferrous metals such as
copper, aluminium, lead, tin, zinc and nickel.
</P>
<P>
Since its founding in 1993, the exchange has gained 121
members. During this period, its total turnover has reached 1.8
trillion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Xiaohong, president of the exchange, said the government
has set prices for non-ferrous metals based on the trading
transactions in the Shanghai Metal Exchange. 
</P>
