<HEADLINE> Avalanche Kills Boy in Bulgaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, January 2 (Xinhua) -- A 12-year-old boy died and 11
others survived an avalanche today in Bulgaria's southwestern
mountain area.
</P>
<P>
The Bulgarian News Agency said the avalanche happened at 11
a.m. when 12 skiers were walking at the foot of a mountain. All
the skiers were buried under the snow, including the dead boy,
Stefan Vasiliev.
</P>
<P>
The local government organized a rescue team immediately in
which 60 skiers and volunteers were involved.
</P>
<P>
By the noon, 11 skiers had been rescued, one of whom was
injured. Half an hour later, Vasiliev was found too, but because
he was buried too long all revival measures were ineffectual.
</P>
<P>
The report said that an avalanche also occurred in the mountain
area last January and a skiing coach died. 
</P>
