<HEADLINE> Stockholm Share Trading Rises in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Share trading on the Stockholm
Stock Exchange rose by 37 percent in 1996. It registered an annual
turnover of 915 billion Swedish kronor (about 136 billion
U.S. dollars), the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The O-list showed an increase of 60 percent. The largest
turnover yet, 270 billion Swedish kronor (about 39 billion
U.S. dollars) was registered during the last quarter of the
year. October was the best month with a turnover of 97 billion
(about 14 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
During the first nine months of 1996, foreign buyers invested
22.8 billion kronor in Swedish shares (about 3.3 billion
U.S. dollars). One third of the trading on the Stockholm Stock
Exchange can be attributed to foreign investors, who hold over 30
percent of the shares. 
