<HEADLINE> Thai Office Property Market to Remain Dim in 1977 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's office property
market will remain dim this year as market supply surpasses
demand.
</P>
<P>
According to the Thai Farmers Research Center, office space
will continue to increase by 800,000 square meters nationwide this
year, although there is already a surplus of 1.5 million square
meters in the country so far.
</P>
<P>
In Bangkok alone, office space this year is expected to rise by
8.8 percent to 6.2 million square meters from 5.7 million square
meters last year.
</P>
<P>
The research center says that most of landlords this year may
opt for no increase in rents or merely 5-10 percent if they have
prime locations.
</P>
<P>
Office rents in Bangkok's business centers currently are
500-600 baht (20-24 US dollars) per square meter per month, while
the rates are 300-500 baht (12-20 dollars) in other key locations
and 250 baht (10 dollars) in the suburbs, it says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970103.0246 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Women Running Greater Risk Of Getting Lung Cancer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Women in China's largest city
of Shanghai who breathe too much smoke produced by cigarettes or
cooking oil run a greater risk of developing lung cancer,
according to a recent survey.
</P>
<P>
Lung cancer caused by excessive smoke inhalation is a leading
health threat to women in Shanghai, with 999 cases of the disease
reported last year, according to information released by the
Shanghai Cancer Prevention and Control Office.
</P>
<P>
The incidence rate of lung cancer among women between the ages
of 40 and 59 has increased rapidly in the past three years. The
number of new cases among women is nearly equal to the figure for
men, who commonly are more at risk of developing lung cancer, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Experts have suggested people use range hoods in their
kitchens, ventilate cooking areas, and avoid frying food -- the
most popular method of preparing Chinese food.
</P>
<P>
Although the city has launched a campaign to ban smoking in
public places from last year, experts continue to urge people to
reduce passive smoking.
</P>
<P>
Cancer prevention and control institutes in Shanghai, Tianjin,
Harbin and Shenyang will jointly carry out a program aiming at
preventing lung cancer in Chinese cities this year, the report
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
