<DOCNO> XIE19970103.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-European Container Ship Making Maiden Voyage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, January 3 (Xinhua) -- The route for oceangoing
container ships sailing between the port city of Ningbo in east
China's Zhejiang Province and Europe has opened.
</P>
<P>
The "VD AQURIOUS V18W," a container ship belonging to France's
CMA Ship Corporation, began its maiden voyage at the end of 1996,
traveling from Ningbo's Beilun Port to Europe.
</P>
<P>
CMA is the fourth largest ship company in Europe, and
fourteenth in the world. The AQURIOUS is capable of carrying 3,961
standard containers at a speed of 23.7 knots per hour.
</P>
<P>
The ship will call at Hong Kong, Singapore, Port Said,
Le Havre, and Hamburg, and finally arrive at Antwerp in the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Ningbo City government said Beilun Port is
trying to open more container shipping routes to overseas ports.
</P>
<P>
Ningbo currently has shipping routes to the United States, and
will open routes to Europe and Canada in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
