<HEADLINE> Increasing Contacts Between Shanghai, Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, the largest city in
China, has launched 351 projects for promoting exchanges with
Taiwan over the past year, according to the Shanghai municipal
government.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Municipal Taiwan Affairs Office said that
these are broadening and that contacts are increasing.
</P>
<P>
Educational exchanges account for the bulk, with cooperation
between middle schools and even kindergartens on the increase. Ten
schools were established in the metropolis with donations from
Taiwan last year.
</P>
<P>
Cultural and artistic exchanges have also taken a major step
forward. The Shanghai Ethnic Orchestra and Shanghai Jazz Band
staged performances in Taiwan, the official said.
</P>
<P>
He said that Taiwan artists and musicians visited Shanghai, and
ten youth groups from Taiwan visited the city last year.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Shanghai held seven large symposiums that were
attended by scholars from both sides of the Taiwan Straits. Many
academic organizations, such as the Shanghai Municipal Academy of
Social Sciences and Shanghai Municipal Association of Science and
Technology, have established contacts with their Taiwanese
counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Press and publication exchanges, and those of sport and
religious groups have also developed, according to local
officials, and the city, which is an economic and cultural center,
expects to play a more active role in cross-strait relations,
experts said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
