<HEADLINE> Finland Beat Norway in World Cup Nordic Combined Team Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Finland's Jari Mantila and Hannu
Manninen won a World Cup Nordic combined team sprint in Reit Im
Winkl, Germany on Thursday, beating their Norwegian rivals in the
cross-country phase.
</P>
<P>
In the nighttime cross-country sprint, Mantila and Manninen
relayed over the 15-kilometer course in 35 minutes and 1.9
seconds. They scored 216.5 points in jumping earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
Placing second overall were Norwegians Bjarte Engen Vik and
Halldor Skard, who finished 3.2 seconds behind the Finns and
earned 224.8 points for their jumps.
</P>
<P>
Austria's Mario Stecher and Christoph Bieler had the best jumps
of the day, earning 231.8 points, and placed third overall.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's event does not count toward the World Cup singles
standings. 
</P>
