<HEADLINE> Armstrong Resumes Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Former world champion Lance
Armstrong has resumed training after completing chemotherapy,
manager of his French team Cofidis Alain Bondue said in Lille on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"He finished his chemotherapy on December 13 and had a good
rest afterwards," Bondue said. "His morale is excellent. He
covered 120 kms on December 29 in the state of Texas where he
lives.
</P>
<P>
