<HEADLINE> Four Letter Bombs Found at Arabic Paper Offices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 2 (Xinhua) -- Four letter bombs were found
today in the offices of an Arabic newspaper in Washington by the
Saudi royal family.
</P>
<P>
Two bombs were found in the morning and two others discovered
late in the day in the National Press Building, which houses the
London-based Al-Hayat newspaper, numerous other media offices and
a shopping mall, leading to two evacuations.
</P>
<P>
Two of the devices were detonated and the other two were
disarmed in order to preserve evidence.
</P>
<P>
The building, located two blocks east of the White House, was
first evacuated after an employee at the newspaper partially
opened a letter and suspected that it was a letter bomb. Police
found a second suspicious letter when they searched the
newspaper's mail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
